{
  "texts": [
    "The application of these pre-trained networks has resulted in substantial improvements in classification accuracy across diverse fossil types, including vertebrate teeth, microfossils, and larger skeletal structures.",
    "While the use of pre-trained CNN architectures has become the norm, relatively few studies have introduced dedicated architectures specifically designed for paleontological applications.",
    "Instead, there is a growing trend toward hybrid models that combine pre-trained CNNs with other deep learning components, such as transformers or sequential models like BiLSTMs.",
    "These hybrid approaches aim to integrate the spatial feature extraction strengths of CNNs with the contextual processing capabilities of advanced architectures.",
    "Incorporating mechanisms such as self-attention and multi-scale feature extraction has enhanced performance, particularly for tasks requiring the identification of complex fossil structures, thereby reflecting the increasing sophistication of DL applications in this domain."
  ]
}